        <h2>English (en-US)</h2>
        <p><strong>Last Updated</strong>: May 29, 2026<br>
        <strong>Effective Date</strong>: May 29, 2026</p>

        <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
        <p>Welcome to Cyber Palm (referred to as "the App", "we", "us", or "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how the App handles information related to you ("user", "you"), the privacy rights you have when using the App, and the actions you may take.</p>
        <p>The App is developed and published on the Apple App Store by NI JUN ("the Developer"). The App is a cultural reference and exploration tool based on the traditional Taoist "Xiao Liu Ren" (Lesser Six Ren) divination practice. <strong>The App does not collect, transmit, or store any personal data related to you on our servers.</strong></p>

        <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
        <p><strong>We do not collect any personal information.</strong></p>
        <p>Specifically, the App does <strong>NOT</strong> collect, transmit, store, or share any of the following categories of data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Personal identifiers (name, phone number, email, address, etc.)</li>
            <li>Device identifiers (IDFA, IDFV, UDID, etc.)</li>
            <li>Location data (GPS, Wi-Fi, IP geolocation, etc.)</li>
            <li>Contacts, photos, calendar, or health data</li>
            <li>Usage data (taps, session duration, crash logs, etc.)</li>
            <li>Browsing or search history</li>
            <li>Any text you enter in the App, including divination numbers and custom questions</li>
            <li>Your divination history or card collection records</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Data Storage Location</h3>
        <p>All data you generate in the App — including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Divination cast history</li>
            <li>Deity card collection (Album)</li>
            <li>Language preferences and other settings</li>
        </ul>
        <p>—is stored <strong>exclusively on your local device</strong> (using Apple's local persistence mechanisms such as SwiftData / UserDefaults). <strong>This data never leaves your device.</strong> The Developer cannot access, read, or back up this data.</p>

        <h3>4. Third-Party Services</h3>
        <p>The App <strong>does not integrate</strong> any third-party analytics, advertising, push notification, social login, crash reporting, or tracking SDKs, including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Google Analytics / Firebase Analytics</li>
            <li>Facebook SDK / Meta Audience Network</li>
            <li>Apple App Analytics (Note: aggregated download and retention metrics that Apple shows developers in App Store Connect are collected by App Store itself, independently of the App's code.)</li>
            <li>AdMob / Mintegral / other advertising SDKs</li>
            <li>Push notification services (APNs / JPush / GeTui, etc.)</li>
            <li>Crash reporting services (Sentry / Bugly / Crashlytics, etc.)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5. Network Communication</h3>
        <p>The App runs entirely locally and <strong>does not require an internet connection</strong>. During usage, the App does <strong>NOT</strong> communicate with any external server, with the following user-initiated exception:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>When you manually copy the AI Prompt</strong>, you may choose to paste it into any third-party large language model application (e.g., ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini). This paste action and any subsequent interaction with the third-party AI service occur entirely within that third-party application, are independent of the App, and are governed by the privacy policy of that third-party service. Please read its policy before pasting.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6. Children's Privacy</h3>
        <p>The App is not designed for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children. The App is rated <strong>18+</strong> on the App Store. Use by minors is not recommended without parental supervision.</p>

        <h3>7. Your Rights</h3>
        <p>Because we do not collect any of your data, traditional rights of access, rectification, deletion, or portability of personal data do not apply.</p>
        <p>If you wish to delete locally stored divination history or card collection:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Use <strong>Settings → Clear Divination History</strong> to clear cast records only</li>
            <li>Use <strong>Settings → Clear All Local Data</strong> to clear both history and card album in one tap</li>
            <li>Alternatively, uninstall the App in iOS system settings, which will delete all local App data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8. Data Security</h3>
        <p>Because the App does not collect or transmit any data, traditional risks of "data breach" do not apply. The App relies on Apple's standard iOS-level on-device encryption mechanisms; the security of your local data is governed by iOS.</p>

        <h3>9. Policy Updates</h3>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy due to feature changes (for example, if a future version adds account sign-in or cloud sync). Material updates will be communicated via:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>An updated <strong>Last Updated</strong> date at the top of this page</li>
            <li>A notice in <strong>Settings → About → Privacy Policy</strong> within the App</li>
            <li>The App Store version release notes</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Continued use of an updated version of the App constitutes acceptance of the updated Policy.</p>

        <h3>10. Governing Law</h3>
        <p>This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of <code>&lt;JURISDICTION&gt;</code> (e.g., <code>Hong Kong SAR, PRC</code>, <code>California, USA</code>, etc.).</p>

